verbose_text: Together, our results suggest that loss of P4-ATPase activity and TMEM16F OE causes distinct modes of axonal degeneration in ORNs : the former results in gradual and age dependent axon degeneration, whereas the latter causes fast and neuronal activity dependent axon degeneration.
